com.mojang.serialization

Interface DynamicOps<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type this interface serializes to and deserializes from. For example, JsonElement or NbtTag.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    JsonOps

    public interface DynamicOps<T>
    An adapter for a hierarchical serialization format. Clients may use this interface to interact with serialization formats such as JSON and NBT without knowing the specific serialization format being used.

    This interface, along with the class Dynamic, is a low-level serialization abstraction used in the implementation of Codec. The functionality offered by Codec is more easily composed than the fixed interface offered here.

    See Also:
    Dynamic, Codec

    • Method Detail

      • empty

        T empty()
        Returns the empty value of the serialization type. This may be the primitive value corresponding to empty, null, absent, etc, or it may literally be the representation of "no value".

        The returned value must be a singleton. That is, clients are guaranteed to be able to compare instances to empty() using reference equality (==).

      • emptyMap

        default T emptyMap()
        Creates a new empty map of the serialization type. The returned map is suitable for passing to mergeToMap(Object, Object, Object).
        Implementation Requirements:
        The default implementation is equivalent to createMap(Collections.emptyMap()).
        See Also:
        createMap(Map)

      • remove

        T remove(T input,
         String key)
        Returns an equivalent value with the entry associated with the given key removed. The input is not modified.
        Parameters:

        key - The key to remove.

      • compressMaps

        default boolean compressMaps()
        Whether the caller should serialize maps using a compressed representation.
        API Note:
        This setting is used in MapEncoder and MapDecoder to determine whether to serialize maps as a list of values keyed by index.
        Implementation Requirements:
        The default implementation returns false. Implementations should override the default and return true if callers would gain space savings by compressing maps before serializing them.
        See Also:
        KeyCompressor

      • set

        default T set(T input,
              String key,
              T value)
        Sets the entry associated with the given key in the input to the given value.
        API Note:
        Unlike many other methods in this interface, this method does not return an error DataResult if the entry could not be set.
        Implementation Requirements:
        The default implementation is equivalent to mergeToMap(Object, Object, Object), except that the input is returned unchanged if an error would otherwise be returned.
        Parameters:
        input - The serialized map to add the entry to.
        key - The key, as a string.
        value - The serialized value.
        Returns:
        A value equivalent to the input map with the given key set to the given value.
        See Also:
        mergeToMap(Object, Object, Object)

      • update

        default T update(T input,
                 String key,
                 (T) -> T function)
        Sets the entry associated with the given key in the input to a value computed using the existing value associated with that key. If there is no existing entry associated with the given key, the map is returned unchanged.
        API Note:
        Unlike many other methods in this interface, this method does not return an error DataResult if the entry could not be set.
        Implementation Requirements:
        The default implementation extracts the existing value from the map using get(Object, String), then sets a new value using set(Object, String, Object).
        Parameters:
        input - The seraialized map to set the entry to.
        key - The key, as a string.
        function - A function which computes a new value using the existing value.
        Returns:
        A value equivalent to the input map, with the new value associated with the given key.

      • updateGeneric

        default T updateGeneric(T input,
                        T key,
                        (T) -> T function)
        Sets the entry associated with the given key in the input to a value computed using the existing value associated with that key. If there is no existing entry associated with the given key, the map is returned unchanged.
        API Note:
        Unlike many other methods in this interface, this method does not return an error DataResult if the entry could not be set.
        Implementation Requirements:
        The default implementation extracts the existing value from the map using getGeneric(Object, Object), then sets a new value using mergeToMap(Object, Object, Object).
        Parameters:
        input - The seraialized map to set the entry to.
        key - The serialized key.
        function - A function which computes a new value using the existing value.
        Returns:
        A value equivalent to the input map, with the new value associated with the given key.

      • convertList

        default <U> U convertList(DynamicOps<U> outOps,
                          T input)
        Converts a serialized list of values of the serialized type to another serialized type.
        Implementation Requirements:
        The default implementation extracts all elements using getStream(Object), then converts each element of the input list using convertTo(DynamicOps, Object).
        Type Parameters:
        U - The output type.
        Parameters:
        outOps - The DynamicOps for the output type.
        input - The serialized list.
        Returns:
        The serialized list converted to the output type.
        See Also:
        convertTo(DynamicOps, Object)

      • convertMap

        default <U> U convertMap(DynamicOps<U> outOps,
                         T input)
        Converts a serialized map of entries of the serialized type to another serialized type.
        Implementation Requirements:
        The default implementation extracts all entries using getMapValues(Object), then converts each key and value using convertTo(DynamicOps, Object).
        Type Parameters:
        U - The output type.
        Parameters:
        outOps - The DynamicOps for the output type.
        input - The serialized map.
        Returns:
        The serialized map converted to the output type.
        See Also:
        convertTo(DynamicOps, Object)
